Fix error messaging to better respond to API errors

No longer use "could not identify audio" as the fallback so that users won't think Shazam could not identify when the web request failed.
Update device list combo box if device list changes
Protect against potential crashes when retrieving the selected device
+Categories in the device dropdown to separate input and output devices

Add setting for whether or not to display input devices

False by default due to the niche nature of the feature, but if you need to give the app audio via microphone, the option is now available.
Rename the device list variables in DeviceProvider for clarity

Use the Shazam v2/detect endpoint

We don't need any of the new features which seem to be based around making a smarter attempt at multiple attempts of identifying a song.

Due to the nature of the recorder, there wouldn't be a good way to integrate that into the recorder.

But, the v1 endpoint is deprecated so may as well switch.

Fold ShazamApiKey.json into config.json

Reduce file bloat.
The first time the files are successfully loaded and saved the app will delete the old file and move forward with what's in config.json.
Fix dark mode background image visibility by changing background shorthand to background-color

- Rollback safety and atomicity verification
- Audit trail integration testing

- `characters/migrations/0004_populate_audit_fields.py` - Uses `player_owner` for audit fields
- `items/migrations/0004_populate_audit_fields.py` - Uses `campaign.owner` for audit fields

- Interactive safety confirmations
- Step-by-step rollback process (data migrations first, then schema)

- Pre-migration checklists and safety procedures
- Step-by-step production deployment guidelines
- Post-migration validation procedures
- Performance considerations and monitoring guidance
- Troubleshooting section with common issues and solutions

### Migration Strategy Overview:

- Add `created_by`, `modified_by` fields to Character, Item, Location models

- Enhance name field with standardized help text

**Data Migrations (0004):**

- Atomic operations with proper error handling

### Production Safety Features:
- Comprehensive test coverage ensuring zero data loss

- Performance testing validates migrations complete in reasonable time
- Edge case testing covers real-world scenarios (user deletion, constraints, etc.)

### Documentation Updates:
- Enhanced `docs/development-guide.md` with migration testing procedures
- Updated `docs/database-schema.md` with migration strategy documentation
- Enhanced `docs/deployment.md` with production migration procedures
- Integrated with existing `CLAUDE.md` development workflow
